cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR

This paper deals with the detection and characterization of bots on Arabic Twitter, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the behavioral and network features of bots, which falls under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with the spread of misinformation and sectarian rhetoric, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
